## Testing- `POST /logout` - Logout- `POST /login` - Traditional username/password login- `GET /auth/google/callback` - Google OAuth callback (handles by Laravel)- `GET /auth/google` - Redirect to Google OAuth## Available Routes```}  // ... other RHU fields  status: "approved",  // or "pending", "rejected"  google_id: "123456789",  name: "RHU Name",  email: "rhu@gmail.com",{```javascriptExisting RHU users can also authenticate via Google:### RHU Collection```}  updated_at: "2025-11-22 10:30:00"  created_at: "2025-11-22 10:30:00",  status: "approved",  google_id: "123456789",  name: "User Name",  email: "user@gmail.com",{```javascriptWhen a new user registers via Google OAuth, the following fields are stored:### Admin Collection## Firestore Collections Structure   - If user doesn't exist: Creates new admin account   - If user exists in rhu collection: RHU login   - If user exists in admin collection: Admin login5. **User Processing**: 4. **Callback**: Google redirects to `auth/google/callback`3. **User Authenticates**: User signs in with their Google account2. **Google Redirect**: User is redirected to Google's OAuth consent screen1. **User clicks "Login with Google"**: Redirects to `auth.google` route## How It Works```</div>    </a>        <i class="fab fa-google"></i> Sign in with Google    <a href="{{ route('auth.google') }}" class="btn btn-outline-primary w-100"><div class="mt-3">```htmlOr with more styling:```</a>    <i class="fab fa-google"></i> Login with Google<a href="{{ route('auth.google') }}" class="btn btn-primary">```htmlAdd this button to your login view (`resources/views/auth/login.blade.php`):### Login with Google Button## Step 5: Use Google OAuth in Your App```],    'redirect' => env('GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI', 'http://localhost:8000/auth/google/callback'),    'client_secret' => env('GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET'),    'client_id' => env('GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID'),'google' => [```phpThe `config/services.php` file has been updated with Google OAuth configuration:## Step 4: Update Configuration```GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://yourdomain.com/auth/google/callback```envFor production, update the redirect URI to match your domain:```GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8000/auth/google/callbackGOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_hereGOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here```envUpdate your `.env` file with Google OAuth credentials:## Step 3: Configure Environment Variables   - Copy the Client ID and Client Secret     - `https://yourdomain.com/auth/google/callback` (for production)     - `http://localhost:8000/auth/google/callback` (for local development)   - Add Authorized redirect URIs:   - Choose "Web application"   - Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth 2.0 Client ID"   - Go to "APIs & Services" > "Credentials"4. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials:   - Click "Enable"   - Search for "Google+ API"   - Go to "APIs & Services" > "Library"3. Enable the Google+ API:2. Create a new project or select an existing one1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)## Step 2: Get Google OAuth Credentials```composer require laravel/socialite```bashRun the following command in your project directory:## Step 1: Install Laravel Socialite- Google OAuth credentials from Google Cloud Console- Laravel Socialite package (`laravel/socialite` ^5.12)## PrerequisitesThis guide explains how to set up Google OAuth authentication for your Laravel application using Laravel Socialite.## OverviewAPP_KEY=
APP_DEBUG=true
APP_URL=http://localhost

APP_LOCALE=en
APP_FALLBACK_LOCALE=en
APP_FAKER_LOCALE=en_US

APP_MAINTENANCE_DRIVER=file
# APP_MAINTENANCE_STORE=database

PHP_CLI_SERVER_WORKERS=4

BCRYPT_ROUNDS=12

LOG_CHANNEL=stack
LOG_STACK=single
LOG_DEPRECATIONS_CHANNEL=null
LOG_LEVEL=debug

DB_CONNECTION=sqlite
# DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
# DB_PORT=3306
# DB_DATABASE=laravel
# DB_USERNAME=root
# DB_PASSWORD=

SESSION_DRIVER=database
SESSION_LIFETIME=120
SESSION_ENCRYPT=false
SESSION_PATH=/
SESSION_DOMAIN=null

BROADCAST_CONNECTION=log
FILESYSTEM_DISK=local
QUEUE_CONNECTION=database

CACHE_STORE=database
# CACHE_PREFIX=

MEMCACHED_HOST=127.0.0.1

REDIS_CLIENT=phpredis
REDIS_HOST=127.0.0.1
REDIS_PASSWORD=null
REDIS_PORT=6379

MAIL_MAILER=log
MAIL_SCHEME=null
MAIL_HOST=127.0.0.1
MAIL_PORT=2525
MAIL_USERNAME=null
MAIL_PASSWORD=null
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS="hello@example.com"
MAIL_FROM_NAME="${APP_NAME}"

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_BUCKET=
AWS_USE_PATH_STYLE_ENDPOINT=false

VITE_APP_NAME="${APP_NAME}"

# Firebase Configuration
FIREBASE_CREDENTIALS=firebase_credentials.json
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=

# Google OAuth Configuration
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8000/auth/google/callback

